data.title: Back in 2011 when I was starting The Feiring Line through Kickstarter my friend, the videographer, Courtney Harmel (@charmel999 )made me do...
data.meta_description: 422 likes, 24 comments - alice.feiring on December 10, 2023: "Back in 2011 when I was starting The Feiring Line through Kickstarter my friend, the videographer, Courtney Harmel (@charmel999 )made me do an infomercial for the newsletter. In the end I thought it was too long and did a homemade one in my living room--which felt so much more me. But uncovering the archives last night, I was like--this is a piece of funny history, so I had to share. In 2011, I had two books. Since then there's been Dirty Guide to Wine, For the Love of Wine, Natural wine For the People, and To Fall in Love, Drink This. Not quite the Joyce Carol Oates of the wine world, but it does seem like too many wine books! By the way, I made three times my goal on kickstarter in record time, which really gave me the confidence to start up. 10 -years later the TFL still is going strong and has grown and evolved, and yes (!) you should sign up if you haven't. Deets in the bio! #naturalwine #thefeiringline #courtneyharmel".
